info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued July 16 at 11:19AM CDT until July 17 at 7:00AM CDT by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Yellow River at Babcock affecting Wood County. For the Yellow River...including Babcock...Minor flooding is forecast. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL TOMORROW MORNING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Yellow River at Babcock. * WHEN...Until tomorrow morning. * IMPACTS...At 12.0 feet, Flooding is confined mainly to agricultural...wooded lowland and marshes. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 9:45 AM CDT Saturday the stage was 12.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 9:45 AM CDT Saturday was 12.1 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage later on tonight. - Flood stage is 12.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Please report observed flooding to local emergency services or law enforcement and request they pass this information to the National Weather Service when you can do so safely. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued late tonight.
